tand contemporary problems such as deaths in custody, high imprisonment rates, police brutality and the high levels of violence in some Indigenous communities. Prioritising the voices of Indigenous peoples, the work will make a significant contribution to the development of a decolonising criminology and will be of wide interest.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aCriminal justice, Administration of. 0aCriminology. 0aIndigenous peoplesxLegal status, laws, etc. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Criminology.2bisacsh1 aTauri, Juan, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertBristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2016z978311119643540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781447321781423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781447321781/original  a978-3-11-119643-5  Bristol UP/Policy Press Complete eBook-Package 2016b2016  aGBV-deGruyter-alles